# Optimistic ID Reconciliation

Optimistic updates are only safe when every optimistic entity has a unique client identity and reconciliation targets exactly one row.

## Required Rules

- Never use `Date.now()` alone, array index, or user-entered text as an optimistic ID.
- Prefer `crypto.randomUUID()` for optimistic IDs. If that is unavailable, add a monotonic counter or another collision-proof suffix.
- Each mutation invocation must reconcile and roll back exactly one optimistic record.
- Batch flows such as “Save all”, bulk import, or parallel creates must generate one optimistic identity per item.
- Reconciliation must not rely on matching rendered text or other non-unique fields.

## Required Coverage

- Same-tick creates produce distinct optimistic IDs.
- Out-of-order responses reconcile the correct optimistic rows.
- A failure removes or reverts only the optimistic entity created by that request.

## Anti-Patterns

- `const optimisticId = "optimistic-" + Date.now()`
- Mapping all rows with a duplicated optimistic ID to the first real server ID
- Bulk create loops that assume requests will not share a clock tick
